I'm having an issue with the default form module. When I leave the form title blank in the module, it still displays an empty H3 element in the DOM. I have some styles on my headers, such as `margin-bottom`. So there's always extra space above the form where this empty &lt;h3&gt; lives. Is there a way to hide the &lt;h3&gt; element if the form title is blank? I am seeing this code in the default form module:

```{% if module.title is truthy %}
	{% set no_title = False %}
{% else %} 
	{% set no_title = True %}
{% endif %}```

Is that supposed to be hiding the &lt;h3&gt; if the title field is empty?
